feedback_text: Jen is a very good facilitator, for instance, Ethan and I did not have our Org cards finished on time, so we all agreed to present what we had so far. Although she made a bit more progress than we did filling out the spreadsheet, she was patient in our explanations as we worked through the sheet as we spoke, she helped us both stay on track for our 3 minute presentation in our group by reciting what was on the sheet as we spoke through the companies pain points and needs in AI. Aside from her technical abilities and skills as an educator, she has shown me such great understanding and love since our first meeting. Her chill energy, genuine kindness, caring spirit, hard work ethic and one of kind advice gives me hope and inspiration. Plus she laughs at my jokes.
summary:
Strengths: Effective facilitation skills. Patience and support in group work. Technical abilities and educational skills. Kindness and caring attitude. Hard work ethic and inspirational advice.

Additional Comments: Jen's positive impact goes beyond just her technical skills, she also brings understanding, love, and inspiration to those around her..

feedback_text: I was able to speak with Sam today and we discussed how we can go about providing better feedback to each other as we move into L2. What was great about Sam's mindset was that he is committed to providing honest feedback to me in person and I told him that I'm committed to do doing the same. It was a great conversation and during the conversation Sam provided brief clear and concise feedback in regards to how he sees me when I talk to other builders one on one. I will use his feedback to improve my one on one conversations with other builders.
summary:
Strengths: Commitment to providing honest feedback. Clear and concise communication.

Opportunities: Continuously improving one-on-one conversations.

Additional Comments: Encouraging to see a mutual commitment to growth and development through feedback.
Strengths: Effective collaborator who enhances team dynamics.
